Session 5 linking fix: WITH_LIBXML=static + WITH_TIDY=static + PHP_CONFIGURE_DEPS sentinel.

Background (see DECISIONS.md ADR-0014):
Session 4 was blocked by the following init-path failure in workerd:
  receiveInstance → loadDylibs → reportUndefinedSymbols → addFunction
  → convertJsFunctionToWasm → new WebAssembly.Module(bytes) → BLOCKED

The root cause is that WITH_LIBXML=dynamic (the upstream default) leaves four
libxml2 symbols undefined in the main wasm binary's GOT:
  xmlStrdup, xmlStrncmp, xmlURIUnescapeString, xmlUnlinkNode

These are referenced by ext/libxml MINIT → xmlInitParser(), which fires during
php_embed_init('embed'). In dynamic mode, libxml2 is a WASM side module
(DYNAMIC_LIBS_GROUPED+= xml-libs, LIBXML_DYNAMIC_LOAD=1). The symbols are
expected to come from the side module at runtime, not from the main binary.

Fix: WITH_LIBXML=static adds lib/lib/libxml2.a to ARCHIVES (statically linked into
the main binary) and does NOT add xml-libs to DYNAMIC_LIBS_GROUPED. The four
undefined symbols are resolved at link time. reportUndefinedSymbols finds nothing
undefined in the GOT → addFunction is never called → workerd init unblocked.

WITH_TIDY=static is required because WITH_TIDY=dynamic requires WITH_LIBXML=dynamic
(enforced by php-wasm-tidy/static.mak). Changing to static links libtidy.a into
the main binary as well. Both libxml2.a and libtidy.a must be pre-built.

Makefile fix: WITH_LIBXML=static removes the only entry that was in PHP_CONFIGURE_DEPS
(packages/libxml/libxml2.so, added only in dynamic/shared modes). An empty
PHP_CONFIGURE_DEPS causes `$(MAKE) ${PHP_CONFIGURE_DEPS}` to become bare `$(MAKE)`
which invokes the default goal `all` → `_all` → infinite recursion. The fix seeds
PHP_CONFIGURE_DEPS with lib/lib/libxml2.a (already built) as a sentinel.

Apply order (from a clean upstream checkout):
  1. patches/session2-fp_async_call.patch
  2. patches/session3-suspend.patch
  3. patches/iconv-resolution.patch
  4. patches/session5-static-libxml.patch  ← this file

--- a/.circleci/.env_8.0.ci
+++ b/.circleci/.env_8.0.ci
@@ -14,13 +14,13 @@ WITH_MBSTRING=1
 WITH_PHAR=1
 WITH_TOKENIZER=1

-WITH_LIBXML=1
+WITH_LIBXML=static
 WITH_DOM=1
 WITH_XML=1
 WITH_SIMPLEXML=1

 WITH_LIBZIP=1
-WITH_ICONV=1
+WITH_ICONV=0
 WITH_SQLITE=1

@@ -39,7 +39,7 @@ WITH_GD=1
 WITH_ZLIB=1

-WITH_TIDY=1
+WITH_TIDY=static

Note: the WITH_ICONV=0 line appears here only because both patches touch the same
file; it belongs to the iconv-resolution patch (already applied).

--- a/Makefile (the relevant Session 5 addition, on top of Session 2 patch)
+++ b/Makefile
@@ after EXTRA_FLAGS+= --js-library line (Session 2 addition)
+# php-wasm-async (Session 5): WITH_LIBXML=static leaves PHP_CONFIGURE_DEPS
+# empty (libxml/static.mak only adds to it in dynamic/shared modes). An empty
+# PHP_CONFIGURE_DEPS causes $(MAKE) ${PHP_CONFIGURE_DEPS} to become bare
+# $(MAKE) which targets the default goal → infinite recursion. Seed it with
+# lib/lib/libxml2.a (already built) as a sentinel to keep it non-empty.
+PHP_CONFIGURE_DEPS+= lib/lib/libxml2.a
